Variola louti (Forsskål)
( Perciformes : Serranidae ).

Anterior attachment organs ellipsoidal, relatively small, approximately 75–133 ( 93 ) in diameter. Three adhesive zones observed in living material (e.g. see
Whittington & Kearn 1993
). Pharynx 41–114 ( 76 ) long, 51–157 ( 98 ) wide. Two pairs of eyespots, pigment shielded, dorsal, between pharynx and anterior margin of body. Unclear whether gut caeca confluent posteriorly. Body and haptor usually heavily pigmented (Fig. 4 ). Pigment ranges from light pink or orange to deep red and occasionally almost black.
